Metadata: Asperazine, a selective cytotoxic alkaloid from a sponge-derived culture of "Aspergillus niger"

Marine-derived fungi appear to be a good source of complex diketopiperazin​es. In this report the authors describe the structure of asperazine, an unusual unsymmetrical diketopiperazin​e dimer, obtained by saltwater culture of "Aspergillus niger" derived from a Caribbean "Hyrtios" sponge.
